Ive never struggled in Stats until this class. Seriously, this prof has no idea how to convey the material. His ppts are long and 50% of the info isnt useful (ex: 18 slides of variations of ONE formula..). The teacher had to curve the midterm & final (each worth 50%) for us to pass. He makes the material SO confusing! Avoid at all costs.

Get ready to teach yourself using extra resources because his lectures make absolutely no sense. Both the midterm and final (each worth 50%) are ambiguous and did not reflect what he taught. I only passed due to the curve. Hes also quite rude and unhelpful too. Save yourself the time and mental energy, do not take him.

Please do not take this professor. I'm being 100% serious. Had to curve both the midterm and the final which is the only reason I got the grade I did (I failed the first exam). Convinced that he has curved every exam he's made. I am very concerned that this professor can continue to teach at the university considering his history of bad teaching.

Choose another professor. Avoid at all cost. He teaches by reading what's on the slides, which isn't helpful. Horrible. He thinks he's funny but comes off condescending. 50% midterm 50% final. Asynchronous, his recorded lectures are him scrolling through the ppt without explaining anything! Im baffled how the university can hire someone as rude, snarky, and incompetent as he is.

Horrible. His teaching style is all over the place and it's hard to grasp material. I've never been so confused in a class before. I'm sorry but if majority of your class doesn't pass your exam, that's on you.

Reused content from previous classes and midterms questions were never seen in class. Every single exam result had to be curved up because of poor grades. DO NOT TAKE THIS PROF! He is the worst prof ive EVER had. He is terrible at teaching and assumes you know everything. Class average is always terrible. The whole semester was just watching long videos of a bunch of formulas with his very monotone voice in the background. He is very rude in his emails and doesn't care about his students. His exams are no where close to what you learn in class. Good luck.

This was a French course, but his mastery of the language is at an early high school level. This is unacceptable, and made content hard to understand. He was completely lost in adapting his course to online learning and his emails were just weird. He got very upset that no one showed up to question sessions and made sure to let us know.

He couldnt figure out how to make his homework accessible during the pandemic, so omitted it halfway through the semester and upped the percentage of the midterm and exam. The midterm had little to nothing to do with the material taught in class. He is uncommunicative, very rude in his emails, and gives no guidance or instruction. STAY AWAY.

Quite rude, treats students like idiots. Basic at teaching, fair in evaluations but just not a pleasant person. Says in class exactly how he will grade and tells you what to expect for the evaluations. Homework is easy.

rComments: If you do the homework and understand the homework its an easy A class.. I think its the first stats class where the homework reflected 100% the midterms. Don't take what he says to heart, and you will be fine!

Awful prof. Very intimidating and often singles out students in class. He made me feel so uneasy that it was hard to even be in the same room as him without feeling a great deal of anxiety. Extremely difficult and unfair exams. Majority of the class got below 50% on the midterm. His lectures make no sense. Only passed due to bell curve.

Could not understand the man. He did not explain the matter in a comprehensible way, I passed the class because I relied on outside sources and tutors. He is not a professor I would recommend for any class. If you take his class get ready to work your ass off!

Horrible prof. Mistakes in at least 30% of his slides. Makes fun of students who don't understand. Not good at explaining anything. Stats is my strong suit but this class was awful. Midterm test was SO long! He is very arrogant. The homework assignments are a good way to bump up your mark. Get ready for statistics

Horrible prof, funny but really sever with correction

He's a funny guy & ok teacher. Go to lectures, even though they are long and he is monotonous. He'll give you clues as to what to except on the exam. He's rude but knows his material, just take everything he says with a grain of salt and you'll be fine. No group project, 5 homework assignments, 1 midterm and 1 final.

Easy exam. Decent teacher. He can however come off harsh if you ask too many questions.

Horrible prof.
